:End Note

Note:
TimeZone primitive KAT.

Coverage:
- timezone_find for UTC, America/Los_Angeles, Europe/London, Asia/Tokyo.
- timezone_find for an unknown identifier returns TZ_ERR_NOT_FOUND.
- Standard / DST offsets for representative zones.
- America/Los_Angeles 2024-03-10 spring forward: 09:59 UTC = PST (-08:00),
  10:00 UTC = PDT (-07:00).
- America/Los_Angeles 2024-11-03 fall back: 08:59 UTC = PDT (-07:00),
  09:00 UTC = PST (-08:00).
- timezone_has_dst returns 1 for LA, 0 for Tokyo.

Exit code legend:
  0  All assertions passed.
  80 UTC lookup failed.
  81 LA lookup failed.
  82 London lookup failed.
  83 Tokyo lookup failed.
  84 Unknown zone returned non-error.
  85 LA standard offset != -28800.
  86 LA DST offset != -25200.
  87 Tokyo offset != 32400.
  88 has_dst predicate wrong (LA = 1, Tokyo = 0).
  89 Spring-forward boundary detection wrong (LA 2024-03-10).
  90 Fall-back boundary detection wrong (LA 2024-11-03).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/time/timezone.runa" as TZ

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: ----- Case 80: UTC lookup -----
    Let tz_utc be proc timezone_find from TZ with "UTC"
    If tz_utc is less than 0:
        Return 80
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 81: LA lookup -----
    Let tz_la be proc timezone_find from TZ with "America/Los_Angeles"
    If tz_la is less than 0:
        Return 81
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 82: London lookup -----
    Let tz_london be proc timezone_find from TZ with "Europe/London"
    If tz_london is less than 0:
        Return 82
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 83: Tokyo lookup -----
    Let tz_tokyo be proc timezone_find from TZ with "Asia/Tokyo"
    If tz_tokyo is less than 0:
        Return 83
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 84: Unknown zone -----
    Let tz_bogus be proc timezone_find from TZ with "Antarctica/Vostok"
    If tz_bogus is greater than 0:
        Return 84
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 85: LA standard offset = -28800 -----
    Let la_std be proc timezone_standard_offset from TZ with tz_la
    If la_std is not equal to -28800:
        Return 85
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 86: LA DST offset = -25200 -----
    Let la_dst be proc timezone_dst_offset from TZ with tz_la
    If la_dst is not equal to -25200:
        Return 86
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 87: Tokyo offset = +32400 -----
    Let tk_std be proc timezone_standard_offset from TZ with tz_tokyo
    If tk_std is not equal to 32400:
        Return 87
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 88: has_dst -----
    Let la_has be proc timezone_has_dst from TZ with tz_la
    If la_has is not equal to 1:
        Return 88
    End If
    Let tk_has be proc timezone_has_dst from TZ with tz_tokyo
    If tk_has is not equal to 0:
        Return 88
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 89: Spring forward 2024-03-10 10:00 UTC -----
    Note: 2024-03-10 09:59:00 UTC = 1710064740 -> still PST (-28800).
    Note: 2024-03-10 10:00:00 UTC = 1710064800 -> now PDT (-25200).
    Let pre_spring be proc timezone_offset_at_utc from TZ with tz_la, 1710064740
    If pre_spring is not equal to -28800:
        Return 89
    End If
    Let post_spring be proc timezone_offset_at_utc from TZ with tz_la, 1710064800
    If post_spring is not equal to -25200:
        Return 89
    End If

    Note: ----- Case 90: Fall back 2024-11-03 09:00 UTC -----
    Note: 2024-11-03 08:59:00 UTC = 1730624340 -> still PDT (-25200).
    Note: 2024-11-03 09:00:00 UTC = 1730624400 -> back to PST (-28800).
    Let pre_fall be proc timezone_offset_at_utc from TZ with tz_la, 1730624340
    If pre_fall is not equal to -25200:
        Return 90
    End If
    Let post_fall be proc timezone_offset_at_utc from TZ with tz_la, 1730624400
    If post_fall is not equal to -28800:
        Return 90
    End If

    Return 0
End Process
